headline: Intel Foundry Is Still Struggling to Win Customers
summary: Intel disclosed that commitments to its Intel 18A process remain minimal.  The launch of Panther Lake on Intel 18A could help sell the process technology to potential customers.  There have been a few high-profile customer wins for Intel's (NASDAQ: INTC) nascent foundry business and its flagship Intel 18A manufacturing process, including deals with Microsoft and Amazon to produce future chips.

headline: Intel Stock Falls as Foundry Customers Hold Back
summary: Intel's INTC) stock dipped after their CFO David Zinsner spoke at the J.P. Morgan tech conference.  Zinsner was quick to note that hitting break-even on the foundry side doesn't demand huge third-party ordersmid-single-digit billions in revenue should do itbut convincing external clients to trust Intel on IP protection and supply-chain security will take time.  Why it matters: If Intel can't drum up external foundry business soon, it risks lagging behind AMD and TSMC just as demand for advanced nodes heats up.
